                <div class="university-about mt-5">
                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Mkhitar Gosh Armenian-Russian International
                        University</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Mkhitar Gosh Armenian-Russian International University is one of the most prestigious
                                government-recognized international medical universities in Yerevan, the capital city of
                                Armenia, established in 1996. Its academic excellence has made the university a favorite
                                place among international students particularly in India who would like to study MBBS in
                                foreign country at a reasonable price and international prestige.

                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>The University is also accredited and registered by the Ministry of Education and
                                Science of Armenia and its MBBS program is registered in top international databases
                                such as WDOMS, FAIMER, ECFMG, and is also acknowledged by the National Medical
                                Commission (NMC) formerly referred to as MCI.

                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Mkhitar Gosh Armenian-Russian International University is a university where one can get
                                a good education in English language, a modern infrastructure, a qualified faculty, and
                                practical clinical exposure. The medical degree acquired at the university is accepted
                                throughout the global world and allows students to participate in licensing exams such
                                as FMGE (India), USMLE (USA), PLAB (UK), etc.

                            </li>
                        </span>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="row mt-4">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-6">
                            <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Why Study MBBS at Mkhitar Gosh Armenian-Russian
                                International University?
                            </h2>
                            <ul>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        No entrance exam, no donation.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Low cost of tuition fees and living as compared to the other European countries.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li> Medium of instruction: 100% English.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        MBBS degree internationally acknowledged (NMC, WDOMS, FAIMER, ECFMG qualified).
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        In Yerevan, a city with modern houses, safe, and student friendly city.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        Hospital training and clinical rotations since childhood.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        Indian cuisine in university hostels and other restaurants.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        Friendly atmosphere with over 500 Indian students who are already enrolled.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        FMGE/ NEXT counseling and local assistance of Indian students.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-6">
                            <h2 class="university-secation-heading">MBBS Syllabus at Mkhitar Gosh University
                            </h2>
                            <ul>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Duration: 6 Years</li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Educational system: The semesters are separated into 12 (2 a year) semesters.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                            </ul>
                            <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Eligibility Criteria:
                            </h2>
                            <ul>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Physics 50%/ Chemistry 50%/ Biology 50% in 10+2 (in general category); 40% in
                                        reserved categories.</li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>NEET is mandatory (according to NMC rules).
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>At least 17 years of age on 31 st December of the year of admission.</li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Should be medically fit (HIV and TB negative reports will be needed).
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
