                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Advantages:
                    </h2>
                    <ul>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>
                                Reduced living as well as tuition fees than most of the western or even certain private
                                universities in the west.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>The ability to use a flexible medium of instruction (English is available) and make it
                                available to foreign students.

                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Exposure to good clinical practice, particularly in late adulthood.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>
                                Recognized state diploma.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                    </ul>
                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Consideration:
                    </h2>
                    <ul>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>
                                Make sure that you are known in your home country and that you are able to pass
                                licensing exams (e.g., in India, see NMC/FMGE etc).

                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Cost of living, visa, travelling arrangement etc shall be considered.
                            </li>
                        </span>
